I've straightened out many metering errors over the years

Apartment 100 is paying for apt 101's electricity

Apt 202 is paying for 203's, 203 is paying for 204's, and 204 is paying for 202's

Hell once the crew that built a 4-story 48-unit apartment building used prints that numbered units 1-12 on each floor from North to South to build the building

Then after it was built the team that numbered the doors numbered each unit 1-12 from South to North

All of this wreaks havoc on electric utility billing, as knowing which unit is paying for which electricity is a paper shuffling exercise. It's humans all the way down. There's no technology available to define it

In today's version, this is happening at a 400 MW power plant üòÇ

This is what the night sky on Mars looks like

When night falls on Mars, the sky turns dark and remarkably clear. With its extremely thin atmosphere, Mars offers a sharper view of the cosmos, revealing more stars than we typically see from Earth

Mars is accompanied by two small moons, Phobos and Deimos. Phobos streaks across the sky in just a few hours, while Deimos moves slowly, resembling a faint drifting star

The Martian sky isn‚Äôt pure black. Dust in the atmosphere often gives it a subtle brownish hue, and near sunset, a soft blue glow can appear along the horizon. On especially clear nights, the Milky Way shines brightly, stretching across the sky in stunning detail

Fix this loophole before the next census makes the distortion permanent.

California's 2.1 million undocumented residents didn't just "happen" to be there - they're the result of decades of deliberate non-enforcement.

The real cost? Law-abiding states lose infrastructure grants, healthcare resources, and political clout. This isn't about partisanship - it's about preventing foreign nationals from dictating America's legislative agenda through proxy representation. Fix the census, restore weight to citizens' votes.
